events.description: Saint Celestine V resigns the papacy after only five months to return to his previous life as an ascetic hermit.
events.html: • 1294 – Saint Celestine V resigns the papacy after only five months to return to his previous life as an ascetic hermit.[1]

events.description: The Council of Trent begins as the embodiment of the Counter-Reformation.
events.html: • 1545 – The Council of Trent begins as the embodiment of the Counter-Reformation.[2]

events.description: Sir Francis Drake sets sail from Plymouth, England, on his round-the-world voyage.
events.html: • 1577 – Sir Francis Drake sets sail from Plymouth, England, on his round-the-world voyage.[3]

events.description: The Plymouth Colony establishes the system of trial by 12-men jury in the American colonies.
events.html: • 1623 – The Plymouth Colony establishes the system of trial by 12-men jury in the American colonies.[4]

events.description: The Massachusetts Bay Colony organizes three militia regiments to defend the colony against the Pequot Indians, a date now considered the founding of the National Guard of the United States.
events.html: • 1636 – The Massachusetts Bay Colony organizes three militia regiments to defend the colony against the Pequot Indians, a date now considered the founding of the National Guard of the United States.[5]

entities.name: Native Americans in the United States
National Guard of the United States

events.description: Abel Tasman is the first recorded European to sight New Zealand.
events.html: • 1642 – Abel Tasman is the first recorded European to sight New Zealand.[6]

events.description: English Civil War: The Battle of Alton takes place in Hampshire.
events.html: • 1643 – English Civil War: The Battle of Alton takes place in Hampshire.[7]

events.description: The English transport ship Duke William sinks in the North Atlantic, killing over 360 people.
events.html: • 1758 – The English transport ship Duke William sinks in the North Atlantic, killing over 360 people.[8]

events.description: Dartmouth College is founded by the Reverend Eleazar Wheelock, with a royal charter from King George III, on land donated by Royal governor John Wentworth.
events.html: • 1769 – Dartmouth College is founded by the Reverend Eleazar Wheelock, with a royal charter from King George III, on land donated by Royal governor John Wentworth.[9]

entities.name: George III of the United Kingdom

events.description: Cyril VI of Constantinople resigns from his position as Ecumenical Patriarch under pressure from the Ottoman Empire.
events.html: • 1818 – Cyril VI of Constantinople resigns from his position as Ecumenical Patriarch under pressure from the Ottoman Empire.[10]

events.description: American Civil War: At the Battle of Fredericksburg, Confederate General Robert E. Lee defeats Union Major General Ambrose Burnside.
events.html: • 1862 – American Civil War: At the Battle of Fredericksburg, Confederate General Robert E. Lee defeats Union Major General Ambrose Burnside.[11]

events.description: A Fenian bomb explodes in Clerkenwell, London, killing 12 people and injuring 50.
events.html: • 1867 – A Fenian bomb explodes in Clerkenwell, London, killing 12 people and injuring 50.[12]

events.description: Second Sino-Japanese War: Battle of Nanking: The city of Nanjing, defended by the National Revolutionary Army under the command of General Tang Shengzhi, falls to the Japanese. This is followed by the Nanking Massacre, in which Japanese troops rape and slaughter hundreds of thousands of civilians.
events.html: • 1937 – Second Sino-Japanese War: Battle of Nanking: The city of Nanjing, defended by the National Revolutionary Army under the command of General Tang Shengzhi, falls to the Japanese. This is followed by the Nanking Massacre, in which Japanese troops rape and slaughter hundreds of thousands of civilians.

events.description: The Holocaust: The Neuengamme concentration camp opens in the Bergedorf district of Hamburg, Germany.
events.html: • 1938 – The Holocaust: The Neuengamme concentration camp opens in the Bergedorf district of Hamburg, Germany.

events.description: The Battle of the River Plate is fought off the coast of Uruguay; the first naval battle of World War II. The Kriegsmarine's Deutschland-class cruiser (pocket battleship) Admiral Graf Spee engages with three Royal Navy cruisers: HMS Ajax, HMNZS Achilles and HMS Exeter.
events.html: • 1939 – The Battle of the River Plate is fought off the coast of Uruguay; the first naval battle of World War II. The Kriegsmarine's Deutschland-class cruiser (pocket battleship) Admiral Graf Spee engages with three Royal Navy cruisers: HMS Ajax, HMNZS Achilles and HMS Exeter.[13][14]

events.description: World War II: The Massacre of Kalavryta by German occupying forces in Greece.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: The Massacre of Kalavryta by German occupying forces in Greece.

events.description: The Knesset votes to move the capital of Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.
events.html: • 1949 – The Knesset votes to move the capital of Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.

events.description: The Mw  6.5 Farsinaj earthquake strikes Iran with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VII, causing at least 1,119 deaths and damaging over 5,000 homes.
events.html: • 1957 – The Mw  6.5 Farsinaj earthquake strikes Iran with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VII, causing at least 1,119 deaths and damaging over 5,000 homes.[15]

events.description: Archbishop Makarios III becomes the first President of Cyprus.
events.html: • 1959 – Archbishop Makarios III becomes the first President of Cyprus.

events.description: While Emperor Haile Selassie of Ethiopia visits Brazil, his Imperial Bodyguard seizes the capital and proclaims him deposed and his son, Crown Prince Asfa Wossen, Emperor.
events.html: • 1960 – While Emperor Haile Selassie of Ethiopia visits Brazil, his Imperial Bodyguard seizes the capital and proclaims him deposed and his son, Crown Prince Asfa Wossen, Emperor.

events.description: NASA launches Relay 1, the first active repeater communications satellite in orbit.
events.html: • 1962 – NASA launches Relay 1, the first active repeater communications satellite in orbit.

events.description: Constantine II of Greece attempts an unsuccessful counter-coup against the Regime of the Colonels.
events.html: • 1967 – Constantine II of Greece attempts an unsuccessful counter-coup against the Regime of the Colonels.

events.description: Brazilian President Artur da Costa e Silva issues AI-5 (Institutional Act No. 5), enabling government by decree and suspending habeas corpus.
events.html: • 1968 – Brazilian President Artur da Costa e Silva issues AI-5 (Institutional Act No. 5), enabling government by decree and suspending habeas corpus.

events.description: Apollo program: Eugene Cernan and Harrison Schmitt begin the third and final extra-vehicular activity (EVA) or "Moonwalk" of Apollo 17. To date they are the last humans to set foot on the Moon.
events.html: • 1972 – Apollo program: Eugene Cernan and Harrison Schmitt begin the third and final extra-vehicular activity (EVA) or "Moonwalk" of Apollo 17. To date they are the last humans to set foot on the Moon.

events.description: Malta becomes a republic within the Commonwealth of Nations.
events.html: • 1974 – Malta becomes a republic within the Commonwealth of Nations.

events.description: In the Vietnam War, the North Vietnamese forces launch their 1975 Spring Offensive (to 30 April 1975), which results in the final capitulation of South Vietnam.
events.html: • 1974 – In the Vietnam War, the North Vietnamese forces launch their 1975 Spring Offensive (to 30 April 1975), which results in the final capitulation of South Vietnam.[16]

events.description: Air Indiana Flight 216 crashes near Evansville Regional Airport, killing 29, including the University of Evansville basketball team, support staff, and boosters of the team.
events.html: • 1977 – Air Indiana Flight 216 crashes near Evansville Regional Airport, killing 29, including the University of Evansville basketball team, support staff, and boosters of the team.

events.description: General Wojciech Jaruzelski declares martial law in Poland, largely due to the actions by Solidarity.
events.html: • 1981 – General Wojciech Jaruzelski declares martial law in Poland, largely due to the actions by Solidarity.

events.description: The 6.0 Ms  North Yemen earthquake shakes southwestern Yemen with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe), killing 2,800, and injuring 1,500.
events.html: • 1982 – The 6.0 Ms  North Yemen earthquake shakes southwestern Yemen with a maximum Mercalli intensity of VIII (Severe), killing 2,800, and injuring 1,500.

events.description: PLO Chairman Yasser Arafat gives a speech at a UN General Assembly meeting in Geneva, Switzerland, after United States authorities refused to grant him a visa to visit UN headquarters in New York.
events.html: • 1988 – PLO Chairman Yasser Arafat gives a speech at a UN General Assembly meeting in Geneva, Switzerland, after United States authorities refused to grant him a visa to visit UN headquarters in New York.

entities.name: Chairman of the Palestine Liberation Organization

events.description: The Troubles: Attack on Derryard checkpoint: The Provisional Irish Republican Army launches an attack on a British Army temporary vehicle checkpoint near Rosslea, Northern Ireland. Two British soldiers are killed and two others are wounded.
events.html: • 1989 – The Troubles: Attack on Derryard checkpoint: The Provisional Irish Republican Army launches an attack on a British Army temporary vehicle checkpoint near Rosslea, Northern Ireland. Two British soldiers are killed and two others are wounded.

events.description: Flagship Airlines Flight 3379 crashes in Morrisville, North Carolina, near Raleigh–Durham International Airport, killing 15.
events.html: • 1994 – Flagship Airlines Flight 3379 crashes in Morrisville, North Carolina, near Raleigh–Durham International Airport, killing 15.[17]

events.description: Banat Air Flight 166 crashes in Sommacampagna near Verona Villafranca Airport in Verona, Italy, killing 49.
events.html: • 1995 – Banat Air Flight 166 crashes in Sommacampagna near Verona Villafranca Airport in Verona, Italy, killing 49.[18]

events.description: Sansad Bhavan, the building housing the Indian Parliament, is attacked by terrorists. Twelve people are killed, including the terrorists.
events.html: • 2001 – Sansad Bhavan, the building housing the Indian Parliament, is attacked by terrorists. Twelve people are killed, including the terrorists.

events.description: European Union enlargement: The EU announces that Cyprus, Czechia, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Malta, Poland, Slovakia, and Slovenia will become members on May 1, 2004.
events.html: • 2002 – European Union enlargement: The EU announces that Cyprus, Czechia, Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Malta, Poland, Slovakia, and Slovenia will become members on May 1, 2004.

events.description: Iraq War: Operation Red Dawn: Former Iraqi President Saddam Hussein is captured near his home town of Tikrit.
events.html: • 2003 – Iraq War: Operation Red Dawn: Former Iraqi President Saddam Hussein is captured near his home town of Tikrit.

events.description: The Treaty of Lisbon is signed by the EU member states to amend both the Treaty of Rome and the Maastricht Treaty which together form the constitutional basis of the EU. The Treaty of Lisbon is effective from 1 December 2009.
